generalInfo.generalRule: No cameras, video cameras, or recording devices are allowed. boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Tickets can be purchased online at www.ticketmaster.com. For customer service please call 1-800-653-8000 during these hours: Mon-Fri 9AM-9PM, Sat 9AM-8PM and Sun 9AM-6PM. For general Target Field information the Target Field Call Center can Be reached at 1-800-33-TWINS or 612-33-TWINS. Hours of the Call Center are Mon-Fri 9am-5pm as well as During all Minnesota Twins live game broadcasts.
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The main Target Field Box Office is located on Target Plaza. Tickets will only be sold in person at the Target Field Box Office On the day of the show. The Box Office will open at 9am on Show days and remain open until the show is underway.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call tickets can be picked up at the Target Field Box Office On show day only during the Box Office hours.

venues.parkingDetail: There are several options for parking around Target Field. Please visit us online at www. twinsbaseball.com/transportation for more information.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Guests with limited mobility may use either of the Drop Off Zones along 7th Street, near both the Majestic Clubhouse Store and Gate 14. No accessible parking permit is required to use these Drop-Off Zones, but these are strictly drop off zones with no parking permitted in either zone. Guests with special needs should refer to the Target Field Access Guide for complete information. This guide is available at all Guest Service Centers, as well as online in the "Target Field"  section of www.twinsbaseball.com.

generalInfo.generalRule: Guests may not leave Target Field and re-enter once they have entered the facility. Target Field is a smoke-free facility. Smoking is no longer allowed anywhere within Target Field or its appurtenant areas. This includes the ballpark itself, Target Plaza, the Promenade behind the ballpark and the 5th and 7th Street sidewalks adjacent to Target Field. Electronic cigarettes are also prohibited at Target Field. There is no re-entry at Target Field.
generalInfo.childRule: Anyone who has had a 2nd birthday is required to have a Ticket for the show. Family restrooms are located on the Main Concourse at sections 111, 123, 132, 134, as well as across from the camera platform above centerfield; in the Grandstand section 238; on the Suite Concourse near Suite 14 and Skyline Suite 2; and on the Terrace Concourse at sections 208, 214, and 220. If a more private environment is desired, please visit the nearest Guest Service Center.

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Sun: Closed Mon-Fri: 10:00am - 5:00pm Sat: 12 noon - 3:00pm
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, Mastercard, American Express, and Discover are accepted.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call can be picked up no earlier than 90 minutes prior to the performance at the State Theate Box Office. Customers must present a picture ID, the credit card used for purchase and the order number.

venues.parkingDetail: There is ample parking in the area. There are flat lots on the corner of 10th St and Hennepin Avenue. There are also ramps located at Marshall Fields, LaSalle Plaza, Target Center, or municipal ramps. The State Theatre recommends using the Hawthorne ramp at 9th Street & First Avenue. The State Theatre is also accessible by the downtown skyway system.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Wheelchair accessible seating is available on the main floor only, as there is no elevator to the balcony. Seating is in Section 3, Rows K and L, and Section 1, Row KK. Hearing devices are available. Please bring a drivers liscense or credit card to an usher to obtain a device.

generalInfo.generalRule: The State Theatre is a gun-free facility. We prohibit weapons in or on our Theatre grounds. Cameras and recording devices are not allowed. Pagers and cell phones must be checked with an usher or the box office.
generalInfo.childRule: Everyone must have a ticket. Children under 6 years of age are discouraged from attending unless the performance is intended for young audiences. Anyone being distruptive will be asked to leave, and no refund will be given. Babysitters may call 612-339-7007 to contact parents. Please be sure the sitter has the seat location of your tickets, since the theatre is not equiped with a paging system. The exact seat location is comprised of a section number, row letter and seat number.

venues.parkingDetail: There are a wide variety of parking options in downtown Minneapolis. ABC/Hawthorne Ramps: There are 7,000 parking spaces adjacent to Target Center in the ABC & Hawthorne Ramps. Downtown Parking: There are nearly 25,000 parking spaces in 38 parking lots and ramps throughout downtown, with most providing a short walk or convenient bus and LRT connections to Target Center. On-street Parking: There are limited on-street, meter-controlled parking spots throughout downtown with pedestrian and transit access to Target Center.
